00:25:22.890 --> 00:25:25.660
And the new emphasis we really
put on in this past year

00:25:25.660 --> 00:25:27.980
was to work with
startups specifically.

00:25:27.980 --> 00:25:30.440
And so Gus' team has had a
big outreach program where

00:25:30.440 --> 00:25:32.830
we try to go and actually
meet with more startups

00:25:32.830 --> 00:25:36.370
like all of you to understand
what information do you need

00:25:36.370 --> 00:25:39.100
to be successful,
and also for my team,

00:25:39.100 --> 00:25:40.910
how can we go and
refine the products

00:25:40.910 --> 00:25:42.940
that we offer to all of you.

00:25:42.940 --> 00:25:44.750
And so what I'm here
to talk about today

00:25:44.750 --> 00:25:46.940
is basically this
idea of iteration.

00:25:46.940 --> 00:25:47.700
Right?

00:25:47.700 --> 00:25:50.220
And here at Google we
got really, I guess,

00:25:50.220 --> 00:25:55.100
famous for having Gmail
as a beta for a long time.

00:25:55.100 --> 00:25:56.910
We didn't know
what color to make

00:25:56.910 --> 00:26:00.150
the links on Google
Search a decade ago,

00:26:00.150 --> 00:26:01.910
so we ran experiments.

00:26:01.910 --> 00:26:03.430
We love to be data-driven.

00:26:03.430 --> 00:26:04.850
We love to iterate.

00:26:04.850 --> 00:26:08.030
We love to try new things, but
also get a lot of user feedback

00:26:08.030 --> 00:26:09.100
in order to improve.

00:26:09.100 --> 00:26:11.100
And we think that that's
something that even now

00:26:11.100 --> 00:26:13.058
that we're a big company
that we have in common

00:26:13.058 --> 00:26:14.550
with a lot of startups.

00:26:14.550 --> 00:26:17.090
And so we want to make it
really possible for all of you

00:26:17.090 --> 00:26:18.960
to be able to do
the same things,

00:26:18.960 --> 00:26:21.410
to be able to gather user
feedback really easily,

00:26:21.410 --> 00:26:23.830
which as you know, is so
critical in the early days

00:26:23.830 --> 00:26:26.930
of your company, and also to
be able to try new things,

00:26:26.930 --> 00:26:31.010
iterate rapidly, and be able
get them out for users again.

00:26:31.010 --> 00:26:34.030
So we really want to
empower all of you.

00:26:34.030 --> 00:26:35.730
And so what we're
going to do is to go

00:26:35.730 --> 00:26:37.370
through a couple of the
different products--

00:26:37.370 --> 00:26:39.411
some of them were mentioned
in some of the videos

00:26:39.411 --> 00:26:42.790
before-- to really talk about
what you should know about

00:26:42.790 --> 00:26:43.620
as a startup.

00:26:43.620 --> 00:26:46.580
And the reason we're giving this
talk is we have a lot of people

00:26:46.580 --> 00:26:48.790
that we run into at
different startup events.

00:26:48.790 --> 00:26:52.160
And they go, beta testing,
I never even heard of that.

00:26:52.160 --> 00:26:54.330
If only I had known.

00:26:54.330 --> 00:26:57.050
Or really, I can reply
to my user's reviews?

00:26:57.050 --> 00:26:58.380
If only I had known.

00:26:58.380 --> 00:27:00.930
And so our goal today is to
try to make sure all of you

00:27:00.930 --> 00:27:05.610
here are aware of the toolkit
that we offer on Google Play.

00:27:05.610 --> 00:27:09.180
So Gus actually introduced
me to this saying recently.

00:27:09.180 --> 00:27:11.300
"If you want to
go fast, go alone.

00:27:11.300 --> 00:27:14.060
But if you want to
go far, go together."

00:27:14.060 --> 00:27:17.610
And what I really like about
this is that what we want to do

00:27:17.610 --> 00:27:21.980
is to go it with you, and
to help you go faster.

00:27:21.980 --> 00:27:24.660
And we hope that through
working with Google Play,

00:27:24.660 --> 00:27:29.974
you'll be able to go together,
and also go twice as fast.

00:27:29.974 --> 00:27:32.390
So we're going to talk about
four different types of tools

00:27:32.390 --> 00:27:34.190
that are the most
unique things that we

00:27:34.190 --> 00:27:36.830
have to offer developers,
especially startups,

00:27:36.830 --> 00:27:38.520
on Google Play.

00:27:38.520 --> 00:27:40.200
So let's get started.

00:27:40.200 --> 00:27:43.660
So Google Play works a little
bit differently, right?

00:27:43.660 --> 00:27:46.100
And I think one of
the things that people

00:27:46.100 --> 00:27:48.390
need to know, especially if
they've been on other app

00:27:48.390 --> 00:27:50.615
platforms before, is
Google Play actually

00:27:50.615 --> 00:27:52.990
has some things that are a
little bit different about it.

00:27:52.990 --> 00:27:54.700
So the earlier in your
life you can find out

00:27:54.700 --> 00:27:56.616
about all the different
features that we have,

00:27:56.616 --> 00:27:58.250
that may actually
change how you want

00:27:58.250 --> 00:28:01.050
to move through your
product development cycle.

00:28:01.050 --> 00:28:03.230
So the first thing
that's important to know

00:28:03.230 --> 00:28:06.040
is that for any of you who
have an app on Google Play--

00:28:06.040 --> 00:28:08.950
does anyone have an app on
Google Play today, by the way?

00:28:08.950 --> 00:28:09.752
OK.

00:28:09.752 --> 00:28:11.960
Does anyone have an app
that's still in Stealth mode,

00:28:11.960 --> 00:28:14.210
or not on Google Play yet?

00:28:14.210 --> 00:28:15.190
A couple folks.

00:28:15.190 --> 00:28:18.480
So we're hoping to reach
you a little bit earlier.

00:28:18.480 --> 00:28:20.860
So the most important
thing for you to know

00:28:20.860 --> 00:28:23.980
is that you can publish your
app on Play any time you want.

00:28:23.980 --> 00:28:25.892
And developers tell
us year after year

00:28:25.892 --> 00:28:27.850
that's one of the most
important things to them

00:28:27.850 --> 00:28:30.040
is that all of you are
in control about when

00:28:30.040 --> 00:28:31.240
you can publish your app.

00:28:31.240 --> 00:28:34.582
There is no big wait
or anything like that.

00:28:34.582 --> 00:28:36.540
And the next thing that
you want to think about

00:28:36.540 --> 00:28:40.540
after that is this idea of beta
testing and staged rollouts.

00:28:40.540 --> 00:28:43.550
So at Google we have an app.

00:28:43.550 --> 00:28:44.490
We have lots of apps.

00:28:44.490 --> 00:28:46.080
And when we release
them, we don't

00:28:46.080 --> 00:28:48.750
want to put them out there
to all the users with just

00:28:48.750 --> 00:28:49.591
the initial version.

00:28:49.591 --> 00:28:50.090
Right?

00:28:50.090 --> 00:28:52.790
What we want to do is
to kind of roll them out

00:28:52.790 --> 00:28:55.880
more progressively and to
get feedback along the way.

00:28:55.880 --> 00:28:57.620
So these two
tools-- beta testing

00:28:57.620 --> 00:28:59.620
and staged rollouts--
are unique tools on Play

00:28:59.620 --> 00:29:01.745
that you can use to make
sure that you get a really

00:29:01.745 --> 00:29:04.290
high quality result,
and also kind of take

00:29:04.290 --> 00:29:05.750
control of your rollout.

00:29:05.750 --> 00:29:08.440
And so we want to walk
you through how this is.

00:29:08.440 --> 00:29:11.310
And what we see from a lot of
our most successful developers

00:29:11.310 --> 00:29:13.990
is they actually use
these products every day--

00:29:13.990 --> 00:29:15.820
the beta testing and
the staged rollouts.

00:29:15.820 --> 00:29:17.920
So for example, at
Google, with but basically

00:29:17.920 --> 00:29:20.502
every app update we rollout,
we use staged rollouts.

00:29:20.502 --> 00:29:21.960
And we think that
even startups can

00:29:21.960 --> 00:29:24.250
benefit from these
sorts of things as well.

00:29:24.250 --> 00:29:25.919
We see when you use
these practices,

00:29:25.919 --> 00:29:27.960
you can end up with a much
higher quality result,

00:29:27.960 --> 00:29:30.800
a higher quality app, and a
much better business return,

00:29:30.800 --> 00:29:32.360
as well.

00:29:32.360 --> 00:29:34.522
So let's start by talking
about beta testing.

00:29:34.522 --> 00:29:35.980
Is anyone here
running a beta test,

00:29:35.980 --> 00:29:38.230
or ever run one in the past?

00:29:38.230 --> 00:29:39.210
That's awesome.

00:29:39.210 --> 00:29:42.050
So we actually see with some
of our most popular apps--

00:29:42.050 --> 00:29:44.970
the top 1,000 apps on
Google Play-- 60% of them

00:29:44.970 --> 00:29:46.960
are running a beta
test right now.

00:29:46.960 --> 00:29:49.370
And so if you haven't
tried a beta test before,

00:29:49.370 --> 00:29:51.180
here's basically the idea.

00:29:51.180 --> 00:29:53.810
You can distribute your
app to a subset of users.

00:29:53.810 --> 00:29:55.540
And then you can get
feedback earlier,

00:29:55.540 --> 00:29:57.960
rather than just
launching it to everyone.

00:29:57.960 --> 00:30:00.140
With beta testing,
what's important

00:30:00.140 --> 00:30:02.650
here is users actually
need to opt in and say yes,

00:30:02.650 --> 00:30:04.270
I want to be a tester.

00:30:04.270 --> 00:30:06.052
And so this can be
really important,

00:30:06.052 --> 00:30:07.760
because it's not going
to be a completely

00:30:07.760 --> 00:30:09.120
representative sample.

00:30:09.120 --> 00:30:11.840
But it will be kind of
self-selecting power users--

00:30:11.840 --> 00:30:13.650
people who are willing
to put up with bugs,

00:30:13.650 --> 00:30:15.360
and ideally also
give you feedback

00:30:15.360 --> 00:30:17.106
about how you need to improve.

00:30:17.106 --> 00:30:18.730
So you can test two
different versions.

00:30:18.730 --> 00:30:20.530
We call them alpha and beta.

00:30:20.530 --> 00:30:22.510
You can view stats about them.

00:30:22.510 --> 00:30:24.520
And it's a great
thing to do before you

00:30:24.520 --> 00:30:26.520
rollout in production.

00:30:26.520 --> 00:30:28.910
So let's talk about some of
the unique features here.

00:30:28.910 --> 00:30:32.240
So users who are in a beta
or alpha test cannot actually

00:30:32.240 --> 00:30:33.940
leave you a review.

00:30:33.940 --> 00:30:34.830
So this is important.

00:30:34.830 --> 00:30:36.890
You don't want them
to leak anything

00:30:36.890 --> 00:30:38.600
or to hurt your star rating.

00:30:38.600 --> 00:30:39.400
That won't happen.

00:30:39.400 --> 00:30:41.090
If someone's opted
in to be a tester,

00:30:41.090 --> 00:30:43.010
they can't give you reviews.

00:30:43.010 --> 00:30:45.032
So we want to go
through a couple

00:30:45.032 --> 00:30:47.240
of the pieces of feedback
we've gotten over the years

00:30:47.240 --> 00:30:49.580
to clear up any misconceptions
that might be out there.

00:30:49.580 --> 00:30:51.460
So the most common
thing we heard from you

00:30:51.460 --> 00:30:55.260
after we rolled out beta
testing was, OK, this is cool.

00:30:55.260 --> 00:30:57.970
But I want to make it a
lot easier to manage who's

00:30:57.970 --> 00:30:59.850
in and out of my beta test.

00:30:59.850 --> 00:31:01.470
So last year we
announced something

00:31:01.470 --> 00:31:03.490
called open and closed betas.

00:31:03.490 --> 00:31:06.090
So if you want to allow
anyone to join your beta,

00:31:06.090 --> 00:31:08.850
you can create what's
called an open beta test.

00:31:08.850 --> 00:31:11.020
This way you'll just be
able to let anyone join.

00:31:11.020 --> 00:31:13.570
And actually as of
this week, now users

00:31:13.570 --> 00:31:16.000
can opt-in directly
to your open beta test

00:31:16.000 --> 00:31:17.990
on your page in the Play Store.

00:31:17.990 --> 00:31:19.610
Your second option,
if you still want

00:31:19.610 --> 00:31:21.650
to keep it in stealth
mode, is to do

00:31:21.650 --> 00:31:22.930
what we call a closed beta.

00:31:22.930 --> 00:31:25.990
So in addition to Google
Groups and Google+ communities,

00:31:25.990 --> 00:31:29.550
you can also specify a
list of email addresses.

00:31:29.550 --> 00:31:32.470
So that allows you to control
only these people get access

00:31:32.470 --> 00:31:35.520
to my alpha or beta test.

00:31:35.520 --> 00:31:37.800
So by the way, if you
haven't checked out yet,

00:31:37.800 --> 00:31:38.900
like that's what
it's actually going

00:31:38.900 --> 00:31:40.210
to look like in the Play Store.

00:31:40.210 --> 00:31:42.940
So for all of you who have
a beta test, an open beta

00:31:42.940 --> 00:31:44.744
on Play, go check it out.

00:31:44.744 --> 00:31:47.160
And then you may want to update
some of your documentation

00:31:47.160 --> 00:31:49.557
to your beta testers
about how they can opt-in.

00:31:49.557 --> 00:31:51.390
And we think this will
make it a lot easier.

00:31:51.390 --> 00:31:53.810
And also for anyone who
already has your app installed,

00:31:53.810 --> 00:31:56.687
if they happen to peruse your
page in the Play store again,

00:31:56.687 --> 00:31:57.520
they might see this.

00:31:57.520 --> 00:31:59.478
And it will make it a
lot easier for you to get

00:31:59.478 --> 00:32:01.960
more folks in your betas.

00:32:01.960 --> 00:32:05.500
Now we mentioned earlier that
when people are in a beta,

00:32:05.500 --> 00:32:07.640
they can't leave
you a review, right?

00:32:07.640 --> 00:32:09.120
Super important.

00:32:09.120 --> 00:32:12.740
And for the whole time that
beta testing's been out there,

00:32:12.740 --> 00:32:14.490
developers can collect
feedback from users

00:32:14.490 --> 00:32:16.250
in a whole range of ways.

00:32:16.250 --> 00:32:19.540
Some people put some sort
of a form in the app itself.

00:32:19.540 --> 00:32:22.220
Others provide an email address
for collecting feedback.

00:32:22.220 --> 00:32:25.030
Other people have
a discussion forum.

00:32:25.030 --> 00:32:27.390
And we added one new
option this week,

00:32:27.390 --> 00:32:31.150
which is that users will be able
to give you private feedback

00:32:31.150 --> 00:32:32.182
through the Play Store.

00:32:32.182 --> 00:32:33.390
So they go to the Play Store.

00:32:33.390 --> 00:32:36.056
And it's in the same place where
they would be leaving a review.

00:32:36.056 --> 00:32:38.134
But it's actually
private feedback.

00:32:38.134 --> 00:32:40.300
So you can see here that
this user in the Play Store

00:32:40.300 --> 00:32:42.860
has provided private
feedback to the developer.

00:32:42.860 --> 00:32:44.667
And when you go into
the developer console,

00:32:44.667 --> 00:32:47.000
you'll be able to see the
private beta feedback there as

00:32:47.000 --> 00:32:47.510
well.

00:32:47.510 --> 00:32:49.220
And again, this is
not shown publicly.

00:32:49.220 --> 00:32:54.720
It does not affect your
app's rating in any way.

00:32:54.720 --> 00:32:58.100
So back to the earlier point
about going fast and going

00:32:58.100 --> 00:32:58.760
together.

00:32:58.760 --> 00:33:00.885
We announced earlier this
week something that we're

00:33:00.885 --> 00:33:02.640
calling Early Access.

00:33:02.640 --> 00:33:05.840
And what this is this is a
special place in the Play Store

00:33:05.840 --> 00:33:07.765
where users, early
adopter users, who

00:33:07.765 --> 00:33:09.640
want to try out the
latest and greatest stuff

00:33:09.640 --> 00:33:13.090
can go to see apps that
are actually in beta.

00:33:13.090 --> 00:33:14.910
And the reason we
launched this was we

00:33:14.910 --> 00:33:16.960
heard from a lot
of startups, wow.

00:33:16.960 --> 00:33:18.780
Beta testing sounds great.

00:33:18.780 --> 00:33:20.720
I'd love to get a bunch
of people giving me

00:33:20.720 --> 00:33:22.500
early feedback on my app.

00:33:22.500 --> 00:33:23.690
But I'm a startup.

00:33:23.690 --> 00:33:25.180
I don't even have many users.

00:33:25.180 --> 00:33:28.430
How could I possibly grow
a group of beta testers?

00:33:28.430 --> 00:33:30.620
So what we decided
to do was to identify

00:33:30.620 --> 00:33:33.900
some of the most exciting
apps that are out there, many

00:33:33.900 --> 00:33:35.400
of them from startups.

00:33:35.400 --> 00:33:37.670
And all of them haven't
really been made publicly

00:33:37.670 --> 00:33:39.890
available on Google Play yet.

00:33:39.890 --> 00:33:42.555
So we handpicked them so
that this way users can

00:33:42.555 --> 00:33:44.430
go there and be sure
that they're finding out

00:33:44.430 --> 00:33:46.638
about really cool stuff
that's actually still working

00:33:46.638 --> 00:33:50.590
pretty well, but be able to get
that feedback to developers,

00:33:50.590 --> 00:33:53.660
get developers like you
a bit more exposure,

00:33:53.660 --> 00:33:55.760
and to help you be able
to iterate more quickly

00:33:55.760 --> 00:33:56.961
and improve your products.

00:33:56.961 --> 00:33:58.460
And this is a great
way that we have

00:33:58.460 --> 00:33:59.830
a huge reach in the Play store.

00:33:59.830 --> 00:34:01.329
And we're trying
to put this to work

00:34:01.329 --> 00:34:03.750
for you to help you find
early testers for your apps

00:34:03.750 --> 00:34:06.090
and get the feedback that
you folks need to improve

00:34:06.090 --> 00:34:10.030
and get ready for
a broader launch.

00:34:10.030 --> 00:34:11.469
OK.

00:34:11.469 --> 00:34:12.219
And then, OK.

00:34:12.219 --> 00:34:13.310
So you have your app.

00:34:13.310 --> 00:34:14.560
You did a beta test.

00:34:14.560 --> 00:34:15.679
You got some feedback.

00:34:15.679 --> 00:34:17.022
It's looking pretty good.

00:34:17.022 --> 00:34:18.230
And you're ready to roll out.

00:34:18.230 --> 00:34:19.868
So you roll out to everybody.

00:34:19.868 --> 00:34:21.909
And then once you've done
that, the next time you

00:34:21.909 --> 00:34:23.690
want to roll out
a new version, you

00:34:23.690 --> 00:34:26.150
can still beta test your
newer versions as well.

00:34:26.150 --> 00:34:28.400
But when you're ready to
put new updates to your app

00:34:28.400 --> 00:34:30.026
out to everybody,
you'll probably

00:34:30.026 --> 00:34:31.734
want to do what we do
at Google, and what

00:34:31.734 --> 00:34:33.260
we see a lot of our
top partners do,

00:34:33.260 --> 00:34:34.820
which is doing a staged rollout.

00:34:34.820 --> 00:34:37.380
So I may not want to roll
out to everyone on day one.

00:34:37.380 --> 00:34:39.429
Maybe I just want
to start with 10%.

00:34:39.429 --> 00:34:41.949
Then I'll monitor the
reviews that I'm getting.

00:34:41.949 --> 00:34:44.010
Maybe I'll use
Firebase to monitor

00:34:44.010 --> 00:34:45.501
the crashes that are coming in.

00:34:45.501 --> 00:34:46.500
I'll see how it's doing.

00:34:46.500 --> 00:34:50.380
And if I feel confident,
20%, 30%, 50%, and then I'll

00:34:50.380 --> 00:34:51.659
roll it out to everyone.

00:34:51.659 --> 00:34:54.219
And here if there's a major
bug, or if people just really

00:34:54.219 --> 00:34:56.710
don't like the new color scheme
my designer came up with,

00:34:56.710 --> 00:34:58.310
I can halt the rollout.

00:34:58.310 --> 00:35:00.862
I can immediately upload a
new version if I need to.

00:35:00.862 --> 00:35:03.070
And then other people who
didn't have the new version

00:35:03.070 --> 00:35:05.260
yet won't be affected by
any negative issues that

00:35:05.260 --> 00:35:07.704
were in my latest update.

00:35:07.704 --> 00:35:09.120
One thing to keep
in mind, though,

00:35:09.120 --> 00:35:10.494
when you are in
a staged rollout,

00:35:10.494 --> 00:35:12.340
people can leave reviews.

00:35:12.340 --> 00:35:15.369
So be sure it is good
before you start that.

00:35:15.369 --> 00:35:17.160
So another trend we've
seen with developers

00:35:17.160 --> 00:35:18.909
is just the amount of
time that all of you

00:35:18.909 --> 00:35:20.839
spend managing your
Play Store reviews.

00:35:20.839 --> 00:35:22.130
So we would talk to developers.

00:35:22.130 --> 00:35:23.171
And they would say, look.

00:35:23.171 --> 00:35:25.070
The more users I get,
the more reviews I get.

00:35:25.070 --> 00:35:25.880
And it's great.

00:35:25.880 --> 00:35:27.520
But I have to have
someone sit there

00:35:27.520 --> 00:35:31.000
and read them all the time, and
then try to have that person,

00:35:31.000 --> 00:35:32.960
you know, summarize
back to the team

00:35:32.960 --> 00:35:36.570
to understand what are users
like, what are they not like,

00:35:36.570 --> 00:35:38.050
what should we do next.

00:35:38.050 --> 00:35:39.430
And so over the
years, we've been

00:35:39.430 --> 00:35:42.630
updating what we have to make
it easier for you to manage.

00:35:42.630 --> 00:35:44.660
So one of the unique
things we have

00:35:44.660 --> 00:35:46.230
is that you're
actually able to reply

00:35:46.230 --> 00:35:47.466
to reviews on the Play Store.

00:35:47.466 --> 00:35:48.840
Has anyone done
that, by the way?

00:35:48.840 --> 00:35:51.000
Anyone replied to a
review on the Play Store?

00:35:51.000 --> 00:35:54.050
Has anyone thought about
it but not done it yet?

00:35:54.050 --> 00:35:55.072
Yeah.

00:35:55.072 --> 00:35:56.030
It's worth considering.

00:35:56.030 --> 00:35:59.320
We definitely see that users
who actually update their review

00:35:59.320 --> 00:36:01.660
after receiving a
reply are actually

00:36:01.660 --> 00:36:04.380
increasing their review
on average by 0.7 stars.

00:36:04.380 --> 00:36:07.540
So it's definitely a good
thing to think about.

00:36:07.540 --> 00:36:08.680
So that exists.

00:36:08.680 --> 00:36:12.510
We've had search on the reviews,
a whole range of graphs.

00:36:12.510 --> 00:36:15.200
We recently rolled out
email notifications

00:36:15.200 --> 00:36:19.206
so that if someone updates their
review again, you can find out.

00:36:19.206 --> 00:36:20.580
So all of these
things are to try

00:36:20.580 --> 00:36:23.920
to make reviews more friendly
to help you be able to dive

00:36:23.920 --> 00:36:26.200
into what's happening
with your reviews

00:36:26.200 --> 00:36:27.809
and how you can
manage them better.

00:36:27.809 --> 00:36:29.975
Because every app that you
get, and every app review

00:36:29.975 --> 00:36:31.170
that you get in the
Play store is really

00:36:31.170 --> 00:36:33.550
an opportunity to have
a one-on-one interaction

00:36:33.550 --> 00:36:34.640
with a customer.

00:36:34.640 --> 00:36:37.250
And I know all of you care about
your users as much as we do.

00:36:37.250 --> 00:36:39.810
And so having those tools
to be able to talk to them

00:36:39.810 --> 00:36:43.400
or understand what's going
on can be so important.

00:36:43.400 --> 00:36:46.830
So this year what we're
just rolling out now,

00:36:46.830 --> 00:36:48.510
and we announced
at I/O this week,

00:36:48.510 --> 00:36:52.280
is automated ways to be able
to extract more information out

00:36:52.280 --> 00:36:53.830
of the reviews for you.

00:36:53.830 --> 00:36:55.530
Because developers
would tell us,

00:36:55.530 --> 00:36:57.456
well, I have to have
someone sit there

00:36:57.456 --> 00:36:59.330
and go through literally
hundreds of reviews.

00:36:59.330 --> 00:36:59.830
Right?

00:36:59.830 --> 00:37:00.700
Not that exciting.

00:37:00.700 --> 00:37:02.920
And then how does that
person report back?

00:37:02.920 --> 00:37:04.980
So we've taken our machine
learning technologies,

00:37:04.980 --> 00:37:07.220
and we're able to
automatically summarize them.

00:37:07.220 --> 00:37:08.990
So we're doing a couple things.

00:37:08.990 --> 00:37:10.700
First of all, there's
certain topics

00:37:10.700 --> 00:37:13.960
that are common across all apps
and we see coming up in reviews

00:37:13.960 --> 00:37:14.890
all the time.

00:37:14.890 --> 00:37:18.620
Things like design,
usability, apps stability.

00:37:18.620 --> 00:37:20.550
And so what we're
doing is automatically

00:37:20.550 --> 00:37:23.440
identifying any reviews that
cite those sorts of factors.

00:37:23.440 --> 00:37:23.940
Right.

00:37:23.940 --> 00:37:26.044
Are people talking
about your app crashing?

00:37:26.044 --> 00:37:27.960
You know, we'll be able
to surface that to you

00:37:27.960 --> 00:37:30.293
so you can just dive in and
see all the reviews that are

00:37:30.293 --> 00:37:31.780
related to, let's say, crashes.

00:37:31.780 --> 00:37:34.416
Or maybe you do a great
new material design layout.

00:37:34.416 --> 00:37:36.290
You can look at all the
feedback about design

00:37:36.290 --> 00:37:39.240
to see if users are
liking your new layout.

00:37:39.240 --> 00:37:41.480
And then a lot of
developers have asked

00:37:41.480 --> 00:37:43.610
us, well, are my reviews good?

00:37:43.610 --> 00:37:44.940
Does my app measure up?

00:37:44.940 --> 00:37:46.690
How do I compare to my peers?

00:37:46.690 --> 00:37:49.060
And so since we're able
to come look at your app

00:37:49.060 --> 00:37:52.520
across these common topics
that happen to all apps,

00:37:52.520 --> 00:37:55.260
we can now actually tell
you how your app's reviews

00:37:55.260 --> 00:37:58.030
in that particular subject
compare to similar apps.

00:37:58.030 --> 00:38:01.240
So for example, are more people
mentioning crashes in your app

00:38:01.240 --> 00:38:02.660
compared to similar apps?

00:38:02.660 --> 00:38:05.820
Are more people mentioning
design, for example?

00:38:05.820 --> 00:38:07.660
And then you can also
see what the impact

00:38:07.660 --> 00:38:09.000
will be on your rating.

00:38:09.000 --> 00:38:11.197
So for example, we
see a lot of people

00:38:11.197 --> 00:38:13.530
if they have a lot of crashes
that users are mentioning,

00:38:13.530 --> 00:38:15.539
that will be dragging
their review down.

00:38:15.539 --> 00:38:17.080
Usually if there's
crashes, it's more

00:38:17.080 --> 00:38:18.592
of a one star type of rating.

00:38:18.592 --> 00:38:20.550
But maybe a lot of people
love your new design.

00:38:20.550 --> 00:38:22.716
And you can see that that's
having a positive impact

00:38:22.716 --> 00:38:24.857
and pulling your rating up.

00:38:24.857 --> 00:38:27.190
And so that can be really
helpful so you can understand,

00:38:27.190 --> 00:38:29.082
if I want to get my
rating up there, what

00:38:29.082 --> 00:38:31.165
are the aspects that I'm
going to need to address.

00:38:34.050 --> 00:38:34.850
All right.

00:38:34.850 --> 00:38:36.480
I want to go back one.

00:38:36.480 --> 00:38:36.980
OK.

00:38:36.980 --> 00:38:37.480
I can't.

00:38:37.480 --> 00:38:42.200
But the other thing I wanted
to mention about it is-- oh.

00:38:42.200 --> 00:38:43.230
That's interesting.

00:38:43.230 --> 00:38:44.155
It was magic.

00:38:44.155 --> 00:38:46.280
So the other thing I wanted
to mention about it too

00:38:46.280 --> 00:38:48.310
is that in addition to
these common topics,

00:38:48.310 --> 00:38:50.850
your app probably has unique
features about it, right?

00:38:50.850 --> 00:38:52.130
Maybe you have a racing game.

00:38:52.130 --> 00:38:53.880
And you have different
types of cars.

00:38:53.880 --> 00:38:55.810
Maybe you have a fitness app.

00:38:55.810 --> 00:38:59.710
And you have features like
pre-programmed workouts,

00:38:59.710 --> 00:39:03.330
or calorie counters, or
instructional videos.

00:39:03.330 --> 00:39:05.560
And so these unique
features of your app,

00:39:05.560 --> 00:39:07.660
we'll also pull them out
with our machine learning

00:39:07.660 --> 00:39:09.440
and natural processing as well.

00:39:09.440 --> 00:39:11.206
So this way you
can also see, OK,

00:39:11.206 --> 00:39:13.330
if I launched a new feature,
like a new type of car

00:39:13.330 --> 00:39:16.450
in my racing game, how often
is that being mentioned?

00:39:16.450 --> 00:39:18.490
And then more importantly,
is that correlated

00:39:18.490 --> 00:39:21.720
with an increase or
decrease in my app's rating?

00:39:21.720 --> 00:39:24.487
So by looking at all
these things together,

00:39:24.487 --> 00:39:26.070
we want to just make
it easier for you

00:39:26.070 --> 00:39:28.445
to see at a glance what people
are saying about your app,

00:39:28.445 --> 00:39:30.130
and also to help you zoom in.

00:39:30.130 --> 00:39:33.060
We hear all the time from
startups, I have so much to do.

00:39:33.060 --> 00:39:34.610
I'm overwhelmed with data.

00:39:34.610 --> 00:39:36.460
Like, just tell me
what I should work on.

00:39:36.460 --> 00:39:38.730
And so we would love to
hear feedback and understand

00:39:38.730 --> 00:39:41.450
if these new reports are
helping you zoom in on what

00:39:41.450 --> 00:39:44.260
it is that you need to do next.

00:39:44.260 --> 00:39:45.190
OK.

00:39:45.190 --> 00:39:46.080
So you have an app.

00:39:46.080 --> 00:39:47.050
You beta tested it.

00:39:47.050 --> 00:39:48.910
Your reviews are
looking pretty good.

00:39:48.910 --> 00:39:52.010
And now what you want to do
is start to go bigger, right?

00:39:52.010 --> 00:39:54.350
And so you want to
build your audience.

00:39:54.350 --> 00:39:56.950
So what we do on Google Play is
we launched the store listing

00:39:56.950 --> 00:39:59.650
experiments feature last year.

00:39:59.650 --> 00:40:02.450
And this is a great way to be
able to optimize your store

00:40:02.450 --> 00:40:02.950
listing.

00:40:02.950 --> 00:40:05.310
You want to know that
it's working well.

00:40:05.310 --> 00:40:07.890
So what we do at Google
is we test everything.

00:40:07.890 --> 00:40:10.750
And we wanted to roll this
out to you guys as well.

00:40:10.750 --> 00:40:12.590
So here are some best
practices with it.

00:40:12.590 --> 00:40:14.530
You want to have a hypothesis.

00:40:14.530 --> 00:40:16.650
You know, is it that
your hypothesis is

00:40:16.650 --> 00:40:21.490
that, your fitness app, people
really like the training video

00:40:21.490 --> 00:40:22.090
capability.

00:40:22.090 --> 00:40:24.740
So you want to emphasize
that, or it's something else.

00:40:24.740 --> 00:40:26.610
And then what you
want to do is to be

00:40:26.610 --> 00:40:28.550
able to run your
different experiments,

00:40:28.550 --> 00:40:31.369
see what the results are, run
it all the way to the end.

00:40:31.369 --> 00:40:32.910
And then a great
thing about startups

00:40:32.910 --> 00:40:35.100
is, if your brand isn't
already well-established,

00:40:35.100 --> 00:40:37.520
you can be pretty bold
in which what you're

00:40:37.520 --> 00:40:38.640
willing to experiment on.

00:40:38.640 --> 00:40:39.139
Right?

00:40:39.139 --> 00:40:40.190
A totally new icon?

00:40:40.190 --> 00:40:41.090
Go for it.

00:40:41.090 --> 00:40:44.540
The big changes are what's going
to get you the biggest payoff.

00:40:44.540 --> 00:40:46.150
So here's an
example of how Rovio

00:40:46.150 --> 00:40:48.430
was able to use a
series of experiments

00:40:48.430 --> 00:40:50.910
to get up to a pretty
significant increase.

00:40:50.910 --> 00:40:52.429
By running these
experiments, they

00:40:52.429 --> 00:40:54.720
had a double digit improvement
in their conversion rate

00:40:54.720 --> 00:40:57.024
on Play.

00:40:57.024 --> 00:40:58.440
And they had a lot
of great things

00:40:58.440 --> 00:41:01.800
to say about how it
impacted their business.

